      <hedline>
        <hl1>'Monday Night' Search Continues</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By RICHARD SANDOMIR</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sandomir, Richard</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Don Ohlmeyer, producer of ABC's Monday Night Football, continues to be cagy about his talent search to replace Boomer Esiason (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Don Ohlmeyer, the producer of ABC's Monday Night Football, continued to be cagy yesterday about his talent search to replace Boomer Esiason.</p>
        <p>During ABC's presentation of its fall prime-time schedule at Radio City Music Hall, he said he would hire one or two new announcers by early June.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Don Ohlmeyer, the producer of ABC's Monday Night Football, continued to be cagy yesterday about his talent search to replace Boomer Esiason.</p>
        <p>During ABC's presentation of its fall prime-time schedule at Radio City Music Hall, he said he would hire one or two new announcers by early June.</p>
        <p>''But don't bother asking who it will be, or, like Tony Soprano, I'll have to kill you,'' he said. He also suggested that ABC add a fourth weekly edition of Who Wants to Be a Millionaire, immediately preceding Monday Night.</p>
        <p>RICHARD SANDOMIR</p>
        <p>PLUS: SPORTS BROADCASTING -- ABC</p>
      </block>
